{"key":"post-11465944","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11465944</id>\n<content>Rye grass seed is inferior to rye berries for sclerotia production.&amp;nbsp; Twenty-five years ago somebody grew sclerotia on rye grass seed.&amp;nbsp; Paul wrote it up in TMC, and since then everybody seems to think that's the only way to go.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Next time use rye berries.&amp;nbsp; Also, if you'll squirt some spores on agar, and then when stones form, transfer a few stones to rye grain, you'll end up with a jar that's over 50% filled with sclerotia after six weeks.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11466019</next>\n<prev>11463351</prev>\n<first>11463140</first>\n<last>11468133</last>\n<when>1258389995</when>\n<utime>11/16/09 06:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}